subproject.description:
The project recognizes the importance of trade and the private sector for poverty reduction and therefore, it aims at supporting the:
1-	Development of a pro-poor/inclusive trade strategy and implementation plan (including National Export Strategy);
2-	 Strengthening of the National trade-policy analysis capacity;
3-	 Establishment of the Metrology laboratory in National Institute of Standardization and Quality, and  capacity building of the respective personnel;
4-	Development and implementation of the pro-youth Growing Sustainable Businesses strategy;
5-	Support selected priority activity areas of the Diagnostic Trade Integration Strategy (DTIS)
6-  Improve livelihoods of the Chibito Millennium Village community through  the establishment of an solar panel irrigation system

